rComments: Really high quality professor, its obvious he is really smart. I had been out of school for many years so I had to work really hard to understand the material. To do well in his class, learn the material from each and every slide and read as much of the book as possible. His lectures all cover a ton of material so attendance is key.
Honestly I found his class confusing. Strangely enough, I always got a higher mark than I expected, even though I didn't know much. Overall, I didn't feel like I learned much in his class.

Got me into finance. He's highly helpful, and actually looks like he cares when he's attending to your questions, whether its online or off. Tests are rather tricky some times, but he marks fairly leniently. Lecture attendance is important despite the fact that he posts lecture material online. He will drop clues about tests during lectures.
best prof ever!!!!!! extremely helpful, respects student privacy and gives really helpful feedback...amazing, my favourite prof!!!!

Excellent prof. Put me onto finance. Wry german sense of humor keeps classes interesting. Beware the course materials are okay, but ur tested outside the box. Stay sharp and its probably the best class in the eco dept.
spectacular prof - knows his stuff, is very enthusiastic and great at explaining. the only problem is that he sometimes forgets that the official language at UofT is english, not german.
He is not the clearest or best prof I've ever had, but he is very helpful and really wants you to learn.
Worst Prof. ever.  Didn't learn a thing!  He is always unprepared.  I don't think he even understands what he is teaching!
